      "writtenOn": "2020-02-27T08:45:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally speaking, if two business objects are distinct from each other in the business logic, they should be separated because there is a chance their properties can diverge in the future. In this CL, metric \u0027resultdb/test_result/count\u0027 is to represent # of table rows under test_results, and all the current fields are generate enough to be applicable to any db tables.\n- table_name\n- row_status\n\nHowever, in the future, if there is a need of reporting certain table specific columns into the metric, then the metric field becomes such a field that is conditionally present only if another field value (table_name) is \u0027foo\u0027, for example. Typically, such metric fields tend to cause unhealthy monitoring configs.\n\nWell, perhaps, I\u0027d propose to rename this metric to \u0027resultdb/db_table_operations/count\u0027 with the following fields\n- FIELDS[\u0027table_name\u0027]\n- FIELDS[\u0027operation\u0027]  # insertion, deletion, update",
      "parentUuid": "bc50de5e_e472733a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 46,
        "endChar": 23
